@node "Secret" "The Secret Part"



                              @{u}THE SECRET PART@{uu}


Aha, so you want to know what the secret pary is eh? Well, all I'll say is
this... It wouldn't be much of a secret if I TOLD you how to find it now
would it? Go and find it yourself, and release a small text file giving
yourself credit for finding it...

Yes I know I could have kept this a MASSIVE secret, and not mention it, but
the way this program works, you wouldn't normally see it, unless you were
to shortcut using the main program and just call up the POKE you want in
it's own sub-directory..

I'll tell you what... If no one has found it by say, the end of January 96,
then I'll release a text file telling you what the secret is, and how to
get to it.... I can't say fairer than that.....

Oh, and don't worry, you don't have to be a hacker, or coder or anything
to get it working. Just a bit of common sense.

Happy hunting!

Rastan.
@endnode

@node "flaws" "Flaws"

                              @{U}HACK ATTACK III@{UU}

                                   Flaws


"Flaws?! FLAWS?!?!" I hear you cry (maybe). Well, yes. I don't want to upset 
anyone, least of all Richard Körber (author of ZXAMPOKE), as I applaud any 
efforts to produce anything for the Amiga (keeps it alive y'see), but there
were a couple of tiny little details I wasn't completely happy about with
ZXAMPOKE.

One main problem was that a lot of the POKEs didn't actually work. This isn't
really anyone's fault as we can't expect the author to have all the games. So,
once I got my eager paws on Speccy Sensations 2, I set about finding which 
POKEs did and didn't work, and then finding LOTS more from mags like Your 
Sinclair (@{B}THE@{UB} Speccy mag!), Sinclair User and Crash. Oh yes, and I also
hacked about @{"300 games" LINK Rastan/Rastan_Hacks.guide/main} myself. Yes, I was a Speccy hacker in a previous 
incarnation (or something)...

Another flaw I found was that I hadn't seen any updates. Which brought me to the
next problem. To bring out an update, you had to send your individual POKEs to 
the author, who would then compile them and bring out another large text file, 
which was basically the same file, with just a few (relatively speaking anyway)
new POKEs.

So, I decided to take a more "Modular" approach to my design, so that anyone 
wanting to bring out more POKEs could do so, and only have to release a few small
text files to patch onto the main directory. {"Click here for more details" LINK "Updates"}

Anyway, almost every POKE has been tested here. I have usually indicated if I 
haven't been able to test it or not...

Oh yes, I also didn't like having to remember what each abbreviation meant.
Yes, I know that's just me being picky, but even after checking EVERY single
POKE in ZXAMPOKE, I found myself still having to refer back to the shortcuts.

Oh well, that's all the faults I can think of (then again, it is 5am), and a
Take That "song" is playing on MTV, so my brain is completely scrambled after
being assaulted by that plastic-manufactured-radio-friendly-teeny-bop drivel!
(And no I don't like them).. I'd rather listen to a C90 of speccy games
loading!

Rastan.
@endnode

@NODE "Bugs!" "Known Bugs"
@TOC "MAIN"

                              @{U}HACK ATTACK III@{UU}


                                KNOWN BUGS



The only thing I can think you may find is that when you select a menu,
selecting "Contents" does not take you back to the start of the main menu,
but rather the start of that particular guide file. I have chosen to do it this
way, as I found that you could end up having multiple copies of the same file
loaded up if you loaded up several POKEs and selected contents, eating up
valuable memory. There's probably something really simple I'm missing, but I
couldn't get the file to work any oter way at all.

If anyone else can find a way of getting it to work then cool.. I don't
mind if you bring out a version with ALL of the POKEs fixed to work properly,
or just a description of how to fix them. If you do fix all of the files,
I don't mind if you add a section at the start giving yourself credit for the
fix, but that is the only part you may edit to that effect. Don't go saying
you wrote this! That really would be lame...

Oh, and before anyone suggests putting a button in, fine. That would work,
but it would mean having to edit about 1000 text files (EEK!), which I
didn't want to do for a feature I didn't think many people would use. I
just use "Retrace" myself in all my guide files..

Apart from that, I can't think of anything else to add. If you do find a
bug like a missing link (ie. you click a button and nothing, or the wrong
thing, happens), then either release a single file fix, or get in touch
with me. @{"Where?" LINK rastan/rastan_CALL_ME.guide/main}


Rastan.
@endnode
